<h2 id="Syntax">Syntax</h2>

<pre class="syntaxbox"><a href="/en-US/docs/CSS/Value_definition_syntax" title="CSS/Value_definition_syntax">Formal syntax</a>: <code><a href="/en-US/docs/CSS/CSS_values_syntax#syntax-single-animation-name" title="none | IDENT">&lt;single-animation-name&gt;</a> <a href="/en-US/docs/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#Double_bar" title="Double bar: The two entities are optional, and may appear in any order.">||</a> <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/time" title="Possible values: a number followed by 's' or 'ms', like 3s, -2.5ms or 0s.">&lt;time&gt;</a> <a href="/en-US/docs/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#Double_bar" title="Double bar: The two entities are optional, and may appear in any order.">||</a> <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/timing-function" title="Possible values: cubic-bezier(), steps(), linear, ease, ease-in, ease-out, east-in-out, step-start-step-end">&lt;timing-function&gt;</a> <a href="/en-US/docs/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#Double_bar" title="Double bar: The two entities are optional, and may appear in any order.">||</a> <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/time" title="Possible values: a number followed by 's' or 'ms', like 3s, -2.5ms or 0s.">&lt;time&gt;</a> <a href="/en-US/docs/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#Double_bar" title="Double bar: The two entities are optional, and may appear in any order.">||</a> <a href="/en-US/docs/CSS/CSS_values_syntax#syntax-single-animation-iteration-count" title="infinite | &lt;number&gt;">&lt;single-animation-iteration-count&gt;</a> <a href="/en-US/docs/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#Double_bar" title="Double bar: The two entities are optional, and may appear in any order.">||</a> <a href="/en-US/docs/CSS/CSS_values_syntax#syntax-single-animation-direction" title="normal | reverse | alternate | alternate-reverse">&lt;single-animation-direction&gt;</a> <a href="/en-US/docs/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#Double_bar" title="Double bar: The two entities are optional, and may appear in any order.">||</a> <a href="/en-US/docs/CSS/CSS_values_syntax#syntax-single-animation-fill-mode" title="none | forwards | backwards | both">&lt;single-animation-fill-mode&gt;</a> <a href="/en-US/docs/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#Double_bar" title="Double bar: The two entities are optional, and may appear in any order.">||</a> <a href="/en-US/docs/CSS/CSS_values_syntax#syntax-single-animation-play-state" title="running | paused">&lt;single-animation-play-state&gt;</a></code>
</pre>

<p>The order is important within each animation definition: the first value that can be parsed as a <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/time" title="The documentation about this has not yet been written; please consider contributing!"><code>&lt;time&gt;</code></a> is assigned to the <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/animation-duration" title="The animation-duration CSS property specifies the length of time that an animation should take to complete one cycle."><code>animation-duration</code></a>, and the second one is assigned to <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/animation-delay" title="The animation-delay CSS property specifies when the animation should start. This lets the animation sequence begin some time after it's applied to an element."><code>animation-delay</code></a>.</p>